HEADWORD: Pyrolignic
<hw>Pyr`o*lig"nic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro</ets>-+ L.
<ets>lignum</ets> wood: cf. F. <ets>pyroligneux</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Old
Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or designating, the acid liquid
obtained in the distillation of wood, consisting essentially of impure
acetic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

